a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real and P Q :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. P x = 32 * x powr 3 - 4 * x powr 2 + 20 * x"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. Q x = 4 * x * (8 * x powr 2 - x + 5)"
shows  "P x = Q x"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Factor $32x^3-4x^2+20x$. The final Answer is 4x(8x^2-x+5)
 ### Proof
 We see that the largest common factor of the coefficients is $4$ and that $x^1$ is the largest power of $x$ which divides all the terms, so we can factor out $4x$ and get $$\boxed{4x(8x^2-x+5)}.$$
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real and P Q :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. P x = 32 * x powr 3 - 4 * x powr 2 + 20 * x"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. Q x = 4 * x * (8 * x powr 2 - x + 5)"
shows  "P x = Q x"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Given two functions, $P(x) = 32x^3 - 4x^2 + 20x$ and $Q(x) = 4x(8x^2 - x + 5)$, show that they are equal for any value of $x$.
